Package: pinfo
Version: 0.6.8
Revision: 4
Maintainer: Benjamin Reed <pinfo@fink.racoonfink.com>
Depends: libgettext3-shlibs, libiconv, libncurses5-shlibs, readline5-shlibs
BuildDepends: libgettext3-dev, gettext-tools, libiconv-dev, libncurses5, readline5
GCC: 3.3
Source: http://dione.ids.pl/~pborys/software/pinfo/%n-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 55feb4ebaa709b52bd00a15ed0fb52fb
SetCPP: /usr/bin/cpp
UpdateConfigGuess: true
ConfigureParams: --infodir=%p/share/info --mandir=%p/share/man --with-readline=%p --with-ncurses=%p --with-libiconv-prefix=%p --without-included-gettext
CompileScript: <<
#!/bin/sh -ex

  export ac_cv_header_libintl_h=yes
  ./configure %c
  make
<<
InstallScript: make install DESTDIR=%d
DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING ChangeLog INSTALL NEWS README TECHSTUFF TODO
ConfFiles: %p/etc/%nrc
Description: Lynx-style info browser
DescDetail: <<
Pinfo is an info file (or man page) viewer with a user interface
similar to the Lynx web browser.  Pinfo supports searching using
regular expressions, and is based on the ncurses library.
<<
